abstract: The Swiss bank's profit plunged 39 percent in the third quarter from the period a year earlier after a rogue-trading scandal had cost it $2.3 billion.
snippet: The Swiss bank's profit plunged 39 percent in the third quarter from the period a year earlier after a rogue-trading scandal had cost it $2.3 billion.
lead_paragraph: UBS said on Tuesday that profit fell 39 percent in the third quarter from the period a year earlier after a rogue-trading scandal had cost it $2.3 billion.

headline.main: UBS Profit Falls After Trading Scandal
